      "writtenOn": "2019-09-18T14:11:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This sort of assumes that the receiver is much faster than iter.Next(). If not, the receiver will always see snapshots as of the last time they received from the channel.\n\nE.g.:\n0s: call iter.Next()\n1s: iter.Next() returns, qsnap is passed to receiver, call iter.Next()\n2s: iter.Next() returns, but receiver not ready\n11s: receiver finishes processing qsnap from 1s, qsnap from 2s is passed to receiver, call iter.Next()\n12s: see 2s\n21s: ... qsnap from 12s is passed to receiver\n...",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 694,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 694,
        "endChar": 14
      },
      "revId": "9fccc35d48e04c6006dcbcb5e2be6f10853ecab9",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a4a1e3aa_a64df7ce",
        "filename": "go/firestore/firestore.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
