        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-09-18T14:34:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do you think this will be a problem in practice?  In the short term we\u0027ll be using the Modified* implementations which should be much faster than QuerySnapshotIterator.  I suspect the slower the receiver, the less it matters if we\u0027re one cycle out of date.  If this *needs* to be fixed, I guess we could implement some kind of snapshot-merging logic, but that seems error-prone.\n\niter :\u003d q.Snapshots(ctx)\nvar snap *firestore.QuerySnapshot\nfor {\n  if snap \u003d\u003d nil {\n    s, err :\u003d \u003c-iter.Next()\n    if err !\u003d nil { ... }\n    snap \u003d s\n  } else {\n    select {\n      case s :\u003d \u003c-iter.Next():\n        snap \u003d mergeSnaps(snap, s)\n      case ch \u003c- snap:\n        snap \u003d nil\n    }\n  }\n}",
      "parentUuid": "37364371_d349b49a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 694,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 694,
        "endChar": 14
      },
